President Donald J. Trump has announced his nominations and appointments for key positions in his administration. Teri L. Donaldson of Texas has been nominated for Inspector General of the Department of Energy. She has previously worked as an Assistant United States Attorney and as general counsel for the Florida Department of Environmental Protection. Michael Kubayanda of Ohio has been nominated as a Commissioner of the Postal Regulatory Commission. He has experience working with the Office of Inspector General of the U.S. Postal Service and the House Committee on Oversight and Government Reform. President Trump has also announced his intent to nominate individuals to the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation and to appoint individuals to key positions in his administration, including the Commission on Social Impact Partnerships and the Creating Options for Veterans' Expedited Recovery Commission.